《'''侍女的故事'''》（{{lang-en|'''The Handmaid's Tale'''}}）是一本由[[加拿大|加拿大]]女性[[作家|作家]][[瑪格麗特·愛特伍|瑪格麗特·愛特伍]]<ref name="Angels">{{Citation | first = Margaret | last = Atwood | author-link = Margaret Atwood | url = http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2005/jun/17/sciencefictionfantasyandhorror.margaretatwood | place = [[United_Kingdom|UK]] | newspaper = The Guardian | title = Aliens have taken the place of angels | quote = If you're writing about the future and you aren't doing forecast journalism, you'll probably be writing something people will call either [[science_fiction|science fiction]] or [[speculative_fiction|speculative fiction]]. I like to make a distinction between science fiction proper and speculative fiction. For me, the science fiction label belongs on books with things in them that we can't yet do, such as going through a wormhole in space to another universe; and speculative fiction means a work that employs the means already to hand, such as DNA identification and credit cards, and that takes place on Planet Earth. But the terms are fluid. Some use speculative fiction as an umbrella covering science fiction and all its hyphenated forms–science fiction fantasy, and so forth–and others choose the reverse. … I have written two works of science fiction or, if you prefer, speculative fiction: ''The Handmaid's Tale'' and ''[[Oryx_and_Crake|Oryx and Crake]]''. Here are some of the things these kinds of narratives can do that socially [[Realism_(art)|realistic]] novels cannot do. | date = 17 June 2005 | accessdate = 2016-07-09 | archive-date = 2021-03-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210325182400/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2005/jun/17/sciencefictionfantasyandhorror.margaretatwood }}</ref><ref name= "Langford">{{Harvnb | Langford | 2003}}.</ref> 於1985年所著的[[反乌托邦|反乌托邦]]小說<ref name ="GradesaverSpecFic">{{Citation | url = http://www.gradesaver.com/the-handmaids-tale/study-guide/section9/ | contribution = About Speculative Fiction | title = The Handmaid's Tale Study Guide | publisher = Gradesaver | date = 22 May 2009 | accessdate = 2016-07-09 | archive-date = 2010-04-19 | archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/5p62J8qGz?url=http://www.gradesaver.com/the-handmaids-tale/study-guide/section9/ | dead-url = no }}.</ref>。小说的标题呼应了[[杰弗里·乔叟|乔叟]]的《[[坎特伯雷故事集|坎特伯雷故事集]]》（The Canterbury Tales）的组成方式，這是個故事集，由某某的故事組成，如「商人的故事」、「帕森的故事」等。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Margaret Atwood on What ‘The Handmaid’s Tale’ Means in the Age of Trump|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/10/books/review/margaret-atwood-handmaids-tale-age-of-trump.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2017-03-10|accessdate=2021-10-25|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Margaret|last=Atwood|archive-date=2017-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170315062426/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/10/books/review/margaret-atwood-handmaids-tale-age-of-trump.html}}</ref> 2019年，系列續作《{{Tsl|en|The Testaments|4=證詞}}》出版。

==故事簡述==
《侍女的故事》由两部分组成，分别是夜晚和其他各种活动。 这部小说可以解释为一个双重叙事，侍女奧芙佛瑞德（{{Lang|en|Offred}}）的故事，以及侍女們的故事。 夜晚部分只是关于侍女奧芙佛瑞德；其他部分，如购物、候车室，家庭等，是描述每个侍女可能的生活的故事。

描述在不久的未来，美國因為戰亂及其他災禍而瓦解，[[极权主义|极权主义]][[基督教重建主义|基督教重建主义]]取而代之。在{{Tsl|en|Republic of Gilead|4=基利國}}，多數女性地位低落淪為雜役，少數仍具備生育能力的則被選為「侍女」（{{Lang|en|Handmaid}}）成為權貴（{{Lang|en|The Commander}}）的生產工具。这部小说探讨了女性在征服中的主题以及获得[[个人主义|个人主义]]和独立的各种手段。

==榮譽==
《侍女的故事》贏得1985年[[加拿大總督獎|加拿大總督獎]]、1987年[[亞瑟·克拉克獎|亞瑟·克拉克獎]]，也被提名1986年[[星雲獎|星雲獎]]，1986年[[布克獎|布克獎]]以及1987年[[普羅米修斯獎|普羅米修斯獎]]。它已被改編為電影，廣播，歌劇和舞台劇。

